  "body": "Related to #139, we'd like to add support for translations of the launchpad.\r\n\r\nHere's my current thinking around sequential steps.\r\n\r\n1. Configure the codebase to support translations (via `react-intl`)\r\n2. Re-work app copy & design to avoid string fragments (which break translations)\r\n3. Refactor all app copy into source language file (i.e. `src/intl/en.json`)\r\n4. Upload source language file (`src/intl/en.json`) into Crowdin\r\n5. Translate files in Crowdin\r\n6. Add translated files (`src/intl/zh.json`, `src/intl/de.json`, etc.) to codebase\r\n7. Add dropdown to site navigation / dedicated page that allows users to select from supported languages\r\n\r\nI welcome input on this. I spiked on a quick prototype to add translation support & will open a PR for that shortly.\r\n",
