    "body": "CC @EthereumCN - saw your comments in #139 & want to loop you in for feedback. I'm looking to help push this forward in the coming weeks. Are you available to collaborate on translation work? I'm thinking we take an approach similar to ethereum.org's by using Crowdin as the primary platform to manage translations.\r\n\r\nLet me know what you think ðŸ˜„ . If you're on board, we'd need some time (a week or 2?) to set up the content appropriately before uploading the content to Crowdin. Thanks!\r\n\r\nI plan to manage the technical side of things to set up translation support in the codebase. @ryancreatescopy will lead the design & content effort to ensure the Launchpad content is 1) up to date prior to translating & 2) structured in a way that facilitates translations easily. @sorumfactory (who leads the Translation Program on ethereum.org) will be available to assist & answer questions related to the translation process. Together we plan to work with @CarlBeek to ensure we're taking all needs of the Launchpad into account.",
